  "local_port": 50876,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I prepare gate 2017 EE after takinng the coaching in 2 mnths i.e frm now? How do I complete the syllabus?",
  "response": "Preparing for GATE 2017 EE in just 2 months after coaching is challenging but achievable with a focused and strategic approach. Here's a step-by-step plan to help you complete the syllabus and maximize your preparation:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Understand the Syllabus and Exam Pattern**\n- **Syllabus:** Download the official GATE EE syllabus and categorize topics into **High-Weightage**, **Moderate**, and **Low-Weightage** based on previous year trends.\n- **Exam Pattern:** GATE 2017 had 65 questions (100 marks) including MCQs and Numerical Answer Type (NAT) questions, with General Aptitude (15 marks) and Engineering Mathematics (13 marks).\n\n---\n\n### **2. Plan Your Schedule**\n- **Divide Time:** Allocate 6-8 hours daily for preparation.\n  - 1 hour for General Aptitude and Engineering Mathematics.\n  - 5-7 hours for core EE subjects.\n- **Weekly Targets:** Set weekly goals to cover specific topics and revise.\n- **Time Allocation:** Prioritize high-weightage topics (e.g., Network Theory, Power Systems, Signals & Systems, Control Systems, etc.) early in the plan.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Study Materials**\n- **Standard Books:**\n  - Networks Theory: D. Roy Choudhury or Hayt & Kemmerly\n  - Power Systems: C.L. Wadhwa or Nagrath & Kothari\n  - Signals & Systems: Oppenheim or Hwei P. Hsu\n  - Control Systems: Gopal or Nagrath & Gopal\n  - Electrical Machines: P.S. Bimbhra or A.E. Fitzgerald\n  - Analog/Digital Electronics: Morris Mano or Millman & Halkias\n- **Short Notes:** Use coaching materials and make concise notes for quick revision.\n- **Previous Years' Papers:** Solve at least the last 10 years' GATE papers.\n\n---\n\n### **4. Daily Study Routine**\n- **Morning (2-3 hours):** Focus on theory and numerical practice for one subject (e.g., Networks or Power Systems).\n- **Afternoon (2-3 hours):** Study another subject and solve problems.\n- **Evening (1-2 hours):** Revise the day's topics and solve questions from previous years.\n- **Night (1 hour):** Work on General Aptitude and Engineering Mathematics.\n\n---\n\n### **5. Revision Strategy**\n- **Weekly Revision:** Dedicate one day (e.g., Sunday) to revise the topics covered during the week.\n- **Short Notes:** Keep revising your notes regularly.\n- **Mock Tests:** Start taking full-length mock tests from the 3rd week onwards to assess your progress.\n\n---\n\n### **6. Mock Tests and Analysis**\n- **Frequency:** Take 1-2 mock tests per week initially, increasing to 3-4 in the last month.\n- **Analysis:** After each test, analyze your mistakes, weak areas, and time management.\n- **Improvement:** Focus on weak areas and revisit those topics.\n\n---\n\n### **7. General Aptitude and Engineering Mathematics**\n- **General Aptitude:** Practice verbal and numerical ability questions daily (e.g., sentence completion, data interpretation).\n- **Engineering Mathematics:** Focus on linear algebra, calculus, probability, and numerical methods. Practice questions regularly.\n\n---\n\n### **8. Exam-Day Strategy**\n- **Time Management:** Allocate time wisely during the exam (e.g., 15 minutes for General Aptitude, 1.5 hours for core subjects, and 30 minutes for Mathematics).\n- **Question Selection:** Attempt easy and medium-difficulty questions first, then tackle the harder ones.\n\n---\n\n### **9. Stay Motivated and Healthy**\n- **Stay Positive:** Avoid stress and believe in your preparation.\n- **Healthy Habits:** Take short breaks, eat healthily, and get adequate sleep.\n\n---\n\n### Sample 2-Month Plan\n#### **Week 1-2: Core Subjects**\n- Networks Theory, Signals & Systems, Control Systems\n- Solve practice questions and revise.\n\n#### **Week 3-4: Core Subjects**\n- Power Systems, Electrical Machines, Analog/Digital Electronics\n- Solve mock tests and analyze performance.\n\n#### **Week 5-6: Revision and Mock Tests**\n- Revise all subjects, focus on weak areas, and take full-length mock tests.\n\n---\n\nBy following this plan diligently, you can complete the syllabus and improve your chances of scoring well in GATE 2017 EE. Good luck!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
